            "text": {
              "status": "generated",
              "div": "<div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">Coronary artery disease confirmed on imaging, management plan established</div>"
            },
            "code": {
              "coding": [
                {
                  "system": "http://loinc.org",
                  "code": "67781-5",
                  "display": "Summarization of encounter note"
                }
              ]
            },
            "title": "Synthesis"
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "status": "generated",
              "div": "<div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">Dear colleague, I am writing to inform you regarding our mutual patient, a 55-year-old male admitted on 31/01/2006 due to abnormal findings on cardiac imaging. Following admission, the patient underwent comprehensive cardiac evaluation including resting ECG, echocardiography, and coronary angiography, which confirmed the presence of significant coronary artery disease. Findings demonstrated evidence of coronary arterial narrowing consistent with atherosclerotic disease. During the inpatient stay, the patient was stabilised medically with initiation of antiplatelet therapy, statin, and beta-blocker. A structured management plan was established including lifestyle modification counselling and cardiac rehabilitation referral. The patient was discharged in a stable condition on 01/02/2006. We kindly request your continued follow-up, monitoring of cardiovascular risk factors, and medication adherence. Please do not hesitate to contact us should you require further information.</div>"
            },
            "code": {
              "coding": [
